HEADWORD: States-general
<hw>States"-gen"er*al</hw> <pr>(st⟦amac⟧ts"j⟦ecr⟧n"⟦etil⟧r*⟦ait⟧l)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In France, before the Revolution, the
assembly of the three orders of the kingdom, namely, the clergy, the
nobility, and the third estate, or commonalty.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In the Netherlands, the legislative body, composed
of two chambers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Statesman</ent>⟦br⟧
